The state girls' hockey tournament begins today with four Class 1A quarterfinal games at the X. The 2A schools begin play Thursday. The quarterfinal games are being streamed on the web by PrepSpotlight TV. You can watch them without charge here. Semifinals and the championship games will be on Ch. 45. Today's schedule: 11 a.m.: Orono 7, Mankato East 1 Iyla Ryskamp tallied a hat trick and Mia Lopez scored two goals as Orono, the No. 2 seed in the tournament, got off to a quick start and defeated Mankato East. Orono had a 43-15 shot advantage, including 16-1 in the first period when the Spartans jumped out to a 4-1 lead. 1 p.m.: Albert Lea vs. Proctor/Hermantown 6 p.m.: River Lakes vs. Warroad 8 p.m.: Luverne vs. South St. Paul On Twitter: David La Vaque | Heather Rule | PrepSpotlight TV You can read more about the tournament here: Girls' state tournament is prime connection to Title IX What's eating at Edina . . . and other state tourney story lines State tournament schedule Meet the 2021-22 all-metro girls' hockey team Vivian Jungels is the Star Tribune metro player of the year Star Tribune high school Live Blog Star Tribune girls' hockey hub Star Tribune boys' hockey hub     